I'll create a 3-bit half adder with a testbench for you. First, let me clarify that a half adder typically refers to a circuit that adds two single-bit inputs. For 3-bit addition, we would normally use full adders. However, I'll create both a single-bit half adder module and then a 3-bit adder using half adders, along with a comprehensive testbench.

